SIMPLE: weaving
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Weaving
<hw>Weav"ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of one who, or
that which, weaves; the act or art of forming cloth in a loom by the
union or intertexture of threads.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Far.)</fld> <def>An incessant motion of a horse's
head, neck, and body, from side to side, fancied to resemble the motion
of a hand weaver in throwing the shuttle.</def>
<rj><au>Youatt.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Weazand</ent>⟦br⟧
